# Communication and markdown

## Code citations

- Prefer **code citation blocks** for existing code: opening fence on its own line, format `startLine:endLine:filepath`. Use `...` inside citations to skip irrelevant chunks.
- Do **not** put list markers or other text on the same line as the opening citation fence.
- Inside fenced or inline code, show characters **literally** (no HTML entities like `&amp;` expecting them to render as symbols).

## Prose and links

- Write like a clear technical article: full sentences, precise, proportional length to task complexity.
- For **web** references, use markdown links with full URLs.
- For **paths** (`https://`, `s3://`, file paths), give the **full** string—do not shorten middle segments for brevity.
- Use **bold** and backticks **sparingly** (only for real emphasis or identifiers).
- Avoid the **§** character in user-facing text (poor UI rendering).
- Skip engagement-style closings; ask directly only when a follow-up is natural.

## Todos

- Mark todo items **completed** when done; do not leave items `in_progress` if work is finished.
